\fs40 \cf4 Why I Suggested 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 api
\fs40 \cf4 \cb1  for launcher-api\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf8 \cb9 gradle\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf11 \cb9 dependencies \{\
    // launcher-api as 'api' because:\
    api 'com.example:launcher-api:1.0.0'\
\}\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 Reason: Both your plugin AND the target app need to see the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 Launchable
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1  interface:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0\cf4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Plugin code needs to cast to 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 Launchable
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1 \
\ls15\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Target app needs to implement 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 Launchable
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1 \
\ls15\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
They must be the same class (same classloader)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 If you used 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 implementation
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1 , the target app couldn't implement the interface because it wouldn't be visible.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs40 \cf4 Better Approach: Use 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 implementation
\fs40 \cf4 \cb1  Instead!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 Actually, on reflection, you should use 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 implementation
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1  for most cases:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf8 \cb9 gradle\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf11 \cb9 dependencies \{\
    // Better: Keep it internal\
    implementation 'com.example:launcher-api:1.0.0'\
    \
    implementation 'commons-cli:commons-cli:1.6.0'\
    implementation 'com.google.code.gson:gson:2.10.1'\
    \
    compileOnly 'com.example:target-app:1.0.0'\
\}\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 Why? The target app should depend on 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf16 \cb17 launcher-api
\fs32 \cf4 \cb1  directly, not transitively through your plugin:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf8 \cb9 gradle\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf11 \cb9 // In target app's build.gradle\
dependencies \{\
    implementation 'com.example:launcher-api:1.0.0'\
\}\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf4 This way:\
